Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6.Place the tomatoes, thyme, garlic and baguette cubes into a roasting tray and drizzle over 75ml/2Â¾fl oz of the oil. Season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Transfer to the oven and roast until the baguette cubes are golden-brown around the edges. Remove the tray from the oven.Increase the oven temperature to its highest setting.Lightly grease a baking tray with a little oil and lay the sardines, mackerel and radishes onto it. Sprinkle over the cumin seeds and drizzle over the honey and 2 tablespoons of the remaining olive oil. Roast in the oven for 5-10 minutes, or until all of the fish is cooked through.Just before serving, sprinkle the basil over the tray of roasted tomatoes, bread, garlic and thyme. Crush the tomatoes lightly with the back of a fork.To serve, spoon the roasted tomato mixture onto serving plates and top each portion with some of the roasted sardines, mackerel pieces and radishes. Drizzle over the remaining olive oil.